# SIZE AND COMPLEXITY LIMITS (REQUIRED)

> Always apply. Every project, every language. Full doc: `{rules_dir}/00-core/size-and-complexity-limits.md`

## Hard caps — never exceed

| Metric | Cap |
|--------|-----|
| Function / method | **80 lines** |
| File / module | **200 lines** |
| Cyclomatic complexity | **≤ 10 per function** |

## Quality Gate — run with every typecheck

Typecheck passing **alone is not enough**. Before marking work done:

1. **Typecheck** — `tsc`, `mypy`, `go build`, project equivalent.
2. **Size** — every changed file ≤200 lines; every changed function ≤80 lines.
3. **Complexity** — every changed function cyclomatic ≤10 (refactor at 8).
4. **Lint + tests** — project linter and test suite.

If step 2 or 3 fails → split/extract in the **same change**. Do not defer.

Optional script: `./agent-harness/verify-size-complexity.sh` (file line cap).

## Agent NEVER

- Ship functions > 80 lines or files > 200 lines without user waiver.
- Skip size/complexity because typecheck passed.
- Skip verification when tooling is missing — count manually.
- Nest deeper to save lines — extract functions instead.

Refactor at complexity **8**; **10** is the absolute ceiling.
